import './App.css';
import { Routes, Route, Link } from 'react-router-dom'
import { Home } from './pages/landingpublic'
import { JobAvailable } from './pages/jobavailable'
import { ApplyJob } from './pages/applyjob'
import { Login } from './pages/login'
import { Navbar, Nav} from 'react-bootstrap'

function App() {
  return (
    //router for the pages
    <>
      <Navbar bg="dark" variant="dark" expand="lg">
        <Navbar.Brand href="/">Job Application</Navbar.Brand>
        <Navbar.Toggle aria-controls="basic-navbar-nav" />
        <Navbar.Collapse id="basic-navbar-nav">
        <Nav>
  <Nav.Link as={Link} to="/">Home</Nav.Link>
  <Nav.Link as={Link} to="/jobavailable">Job Available</Nav.Link>
  <Nav.Link as={Link} to="/applyjob">Apply Job</Nav.Link>
  <Nav.Link as={Link} to="/login">Login</Nav.Link>
</Nav>

        </Navbar.Collapse>
      </Navbar>
      <Routes>
        <Route path="/" element={<Home />} />
        <Route path="/jobavailable" element={<JobAvailable />} />
        <Route path="/applyjob" element={<ApplyJob />} />
        <Route path="/login" element={<Login/>} />
      </Routes>
    </>
  );
}

export default App;
